[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_n06xo")
reagent_id = "NO"
title = "Nitric oxide"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]NO[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]30 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Gas[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Colorless[/cell]
[cell]Smell:[/cell][cell]Slight odor[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
N₂ + O₂ → 2NO
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Reactive gas that easily reacts with oxygen.
• In air it quickly forms nitrogen dioxide (NO₂).
[b]Where nitric oxide is found[/b]
• Produced during high-temperature combustion (car engines, power plants).
• Formed naturally in lightning.
• Also produced in small amounts in the human body.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Used in medicine to help treat some lung conditions.
• Important intermediate in chemical reactions.
[b]Safety[/b]
Toxic in high concentrations and can form harmful air pollutants."
